    base:desc "The DT is organized as a pipeline of distinct services: sensor data are continuously collected from the physical twin, calibration algorithms use these data to update the parameters of cyber models that represent the CPS and its environment, the calibrated models produce information that feeds monitoring components which assess whether the system is operating safely and optimally, and when a violation is detected a decision component (either a human operator or an automated algorithm) triggers corrective actions on the physical twin. This structure integrates data acquisition, model calibration, monitoring, and decision-making in a coordinated sequence."
]

